personalInfo.splInterest: Reading, hanging with friends, going to the lake, basketball

tourBios.carHigh:
Has played primarily on the Hooters and Adams Tight Lies Tour...Has never played in a PGA TOUR event.



2010: Made the cut in two of nine starts on the Web.com Tour. Was T30 at the Mexico Open...Later turned in a T25 at the Mylan Classic. 

2009: Missed the cut in his only two starts on the Web.com Tour. 

2008: Finished T57 at the Fort Smith Classic, his only Web.com Tour start.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Finished third in the Texas State Open...Made his Web.com Tour debut, at the 2000 Fort Smith Classic, where he missed the cut. Missed the cut at the 2002 Fort Smith Classic after receiving a sponsor exemption.
tourBios.personal: His sister, Natalie, plays at the University of Arkansas. Still holds two school records in basketball at his high school...Non-golf related jobs held include working at a tennis club. Favorite golf course he has played is Southern Hills CC in Tulsa, Okla....Would most like to play St. Andrews' Old Course...Never travels without his phone. Favorite college team is the Arkansas Razorbacks. Favorite professional team is the Orlando Magic...Favorite TV show is "Family Guy," with "Rocky" and all of its sequels his favorite movies...Favorite entertainer is Jay Z, and favorite athlete is LeBron James...Enjoys Mexican food and lists Dallas as his favorite city to visit. Favorite vacation spot is Mexico...Would round out his dream foursome with Tiger Woods, Bill Clinton and Michael Jordan.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Web.com Tour was T25th in 2010 at the Mylan Classic presented by CONSOL Energy.
